.SH NAME
\fBconstant\fP \- define a constant global symbol
.\" spec reStructuredText documentation
.
\fP
.PP
.\" @(#)constant.rst     6.1  08/01/12  CSS
.
.\" Copyright (c) 1990,1991,1995,2012 Certified Scientific Software
.
.\" 
.
.\" versioninfo: "constant" "command" "08/01/12" "constant.rst 6.1  08/01/12 CSS"
.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.rs
.sp
\fBconstant symbol value\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.rs
.sp
The \fBconstant\fP command creates (or modifies the value of an existing)
global variable.
The value of a \fBconstant\fP global variable cannot be changed
by ordinary assignment.  An attempt to so results in an error.
.sp
The purpose of the \fBconstant\fP variable type is
to prevent accidental or casual modification of important parameters.
.SH "EXAMPLE"
.rs
.sp
\fBconstant EPOCH time()\fP
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.rs
.sp
\fI\%global\fP
\fI\%syms\fP

